text: Tatjana Steinhauer (born 28 January 1990) is a German water polo player. She was part of the Germany women's national water polo team at the 2010 Women's European Water Polo Championship, and 2012 Women's European Water Polo Championship. At the club level, she played for Hannoverscher SV,Wolfgang Philipps, Sun - Water - Air. 90 years of swimming in Lehrte and Lehrter SV, 1921 - 2011 , Groß-Oesingen 2011, p. 35. and SV Blau-Weiß Bochum. == References == Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:German water polo players
